Update to this 
import type { SupabaseClient } from '@supabase/supabase-js';

type DeleteResult<T = any> = {
  success: boolean;
  error?: { message: string; status?: number };
  deleted?: T | null;
  reason?: 'not_found' | 'not_owner' | 'permission' | 'network';
};

/**
 * deletePost - Service layer function to delete a post safely with ownership pre-check.
 * @param supabase - SupabaseClient (from @supabase/supabase-js) bound to the user's session
 * @param postId - id of the post to delete
 * @param currentUserId - the currently-authenticated user's id (string) OR null for guest
 */
export async function deletePost(
  supabase: SupabaseClient,
  postId: string,
  currentUserId: string | null
): Promise<DeleteResult> {
  try {
    // 1) Fetch the post user_id to check ownership
    const { data: rows, error: fetchErr } = await supabase
      .from('posts')
      .select('id, user_id, nickname, content')
      .eq('id', postId)
      .limit(1)
      .maybeSingle();

    if (fetchErr) {
      // Network or permission to read failed
      return {
        success: false,
        error: { message: fetchErr.message, status: fetchErr.status },
        reason: fetchErr.status === 403 ? 'permission' : 'network',
      };
    }

    if (!rows) {
      return { success: false, error: { message: 'Post not found' }, reason: 'not_found' };
    }

    const postUserId: string | null = rows.user_id ?? null;

    // 2) Resolve caller identity - currentUserId should come from your app's auth wrapper
    // If you allow shadow/guest users, your app should supply the shadow id as currentUserId.
    if (!currentUserId) {
      return {
        success: false,
        error: { message: 'Not authenticated' },
        reason: 'not_owner',
      };
    }

    // 3) Ownership check
    if (postUserId !== currentUserId) {
      return {
        success: false,
        error: { message: 'You are not the owner of this post' },
        reason: 'not_owner',
      };
    }

    // 4) Attempt the delete
    const { data: deleted, error: deleteErr } = await supabase
      .from('posts')
      .delete()
      .eq('id', postId)
      .select()
      .maybeSingle();

    if (deleteErr) {
      // Final safeguard: RLS could deny this even if pre-check passed (race conditions)
      return {
        success: false,
        error: { message: deleteErr.message, status: deleteErr.status },
        reason: deleteErr.status === 403 ? 'permission' : 'network',
      };
    }

    return { success: true, deleted, deleted: deleted ?? null };
  } catch (err: any) {
    return {
      success: false,
      error: { message: err?.message ?? 'Unexpected error' },
      reason: 'network',
    };
  }
}

Notes:

maybeSingle() is used to gracefully handle 0/1 rows depending on client version; if your client doesn't have it, use .single() and handle errors.
This function assumes currentUserId is supplied by your auth layer (e.g., from supabase.auth.getUser() or your session store).
If you support shadow/guest identities, populate currentUserId with the shadow id when the user is a guest.
Frontend usage pattern (optimistic UI + rollback)
Before calling deletePost, remove the post optimistically from state and keep a snapshot to rollback if needed.
Call deletePost; if success -> confirm UI (no further action). If failure -> restore snapshot and show error.

// Assumptions: you have setPosts / posts state and a toast function
async function handleDeleteClick(postId: string) {
  // snapshot for rollback
  const snapshot = posts;
  // optimistic update
  setPosts(prev => prev.filter(p => p.id !== postId));

  // currentUserId from auth/session or shadow id
  const currentUserId = currentUser?.id ?? null;

  const result = await deletePost(supabase, postId, currentUserId);

  if (!result.success) {
    // rollback
    setPosts(snapshot);
    // Friendly messaging
    if (result.reason === 'not_owner') {
      toast.error(result.error?.message ?? 'You cannot delete this post.');
    } else if (result.reason === 'not_found') {
      toast.info('Post already deleted.');
    } else {
      toast.error(result.error?.message ?? 'Failed to delete post. Please try again.');
    }
    return;
  }

  // success message (optional)
  toast.success('Post deleted');
  // Optionally, invalidate queries or confirm data consistency
  // queryClient.invalidateQueries(['posts']); // if using React Query
}

Handling race conditions and RLS mismatches
Even with a pre-check, a race can occur (ownership changed) — the DB/RLS is the final guard. The service handles this by returning a permission error if the delete is rejected.
The UI rollback on any failure keeps UX consistent.
Optional: server-side admin deletes (Edge Function)
If you need an admin path to delete any post (for moderators), create an Edge Function that verifies an admin claim from the JWT (e.g., auth.jwt() ->> 'role' = 'admin') and then uses SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY to run the delete. I can provide a TypeScript Edge Function for that if desired.

